    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This 21-stringed instrument symbolizes connectivity with the past, present, and future. The kora grants a +2 item bonus to Performance checks made to tell stories when used to accompany song or speech.   \n   \n *The kora of the unending story* is a coda instrument\u2014an item that functions like a staff but in the form of a musical instrument.",
        "level": 14,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 137,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
                "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "rare"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Coda",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Treasure Vault",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Treasure Vault pg. 217",
                            "alt": "Treasure Vault pg. 217",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 191
                        },
                        "page": 217,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 191
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9631175884a13a60b9453ab6c7b6b450",
                "text": "Instruments with the coda trait work mostly like staves and have the staff trait. There are two differences: Coda instruments are in the form of musical instruments, and they can be prepared only by bards. Because they're not physically staves, you can't attack with a coda instrument, nor can you etch it with weapon runes.  \n  \n The process of preparing a coda instrument involves playing significant portions of songs related to the spells within the instrument\u2014either old standards or ones of your own creation. This leaves magical reverberations within the instrument that allow you to complete the songs by playing their coda later in the day.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "staves",
                        "alt": "staves",
                        "game-obj": "Rules",
                        "aonid": 748
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "staff",
                        "alt": "staff",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 151
                    },
